data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your synchronous Cosmos DB calls will throw at runtime — no opt-in can save them.**

In .NET 10 you could re-enable sync-over-async with a provider option. **EF Core 11 removes that opt-in entirely.** `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now always throw.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This means callers must also be updated to `await` these methods — the async "bubbles up" through the call chain. Remove any `EnableSyncIo` / sync-over-async opt-in configuration since it no longer has any effect.
